In this article, President Barack Obama issues a proclamation for Labor Day, recognizing the contributions and importance of American workers. He highlights the role of workers in shaping the nation's economic success and prosperity, from building infrastructure to driving innovation. The president acknowledges the historical struggles and achievements of workers in gaining fair pay, better benefits, and safer working conditions. He also acknowledges the challenges faced by workers during the recent recession and emphasizes the importance of job training and investing in industries that cannot be outsourced. President Obama expresses confidence in the American economy and honors the resolve and resilience of American workers. The proclamation calls upon public officials and the people of the United States to observe Labor Day with programs and activities that acknowledge the contributions of working Americans and their families.